I get asked all the time about my houseplants and these are my top three:
• polka dot begonia / begonia maculata : I just love the unique shape, leaf design, and leaf color. All it wants is a decent mount of light, regular watering, and occasional fertilizing. 
• angel wing begonia / benigo pink variety: the way the leave glow crimson when the sun passes through them adds so much warmth to my living room. Same care as above + removing dead leaves. 
• myrtle topiary: I love this little guy and the look it gives my space. Water every other day, plenty of bright light, and regular trimming/shaping. 

I’ve owned all of these plants for over a year and have found them to be relatively easy to care for. Good luck finding your perfect plants!
#houseplants #plants #plantsofinstagram #plantsplantsplants #plantslover

Life is magical.

This morning I looked up from my book to see my little girls doing the same. Different issues of Country Living, same proud stack, endless dreams and possibilities.

If you don’t already know it, let me tell you the story of how this house became The Adored House… Just about 7 years ago, we bought a 5 year old, totally beige, characterless house. The day my husband twisted my arm so that I would say “yes” to this house, I sobbed for a solid hour because this wasn’t the house I envisioned as our forever home at all. I wanted something old and charming with mature gardens, but the “old and charmings” we were finding didn’t check off the practical boxes like newish appliances, quiet streets, and great schools. So, I settled for the boring beige house on the quiet street that my kids could ride their bikes on. Since day one, I worked tirelessly to make this house reflect the character and details I admire about old houses. All of that work has resulted in a home that we truly love and the realization of a dream I have had since I was a little girl…in about 2 weeks our home will be photographed for the Summer 2024 issue of @countryhomemagazine. I have been so quiet about this news because I’ve had a touch of imposter syndrome and a mile long list of to-dos to prepare the house, but the shoot is almost here and I cannot wait to take you along for the ride. Thank you for being here and sharing this joy with me. 🤍D

#currenthomeview #cljsquad #cottagestyle #countryhome

Lately I have been very occupied with the joys of being a mom and owning my own business - two passions of mine that fuel one another. While I haven’t been doing much around the house besides vacuuming and making beds, I am so grateful for the time I took to make this home a comfortable retreat for my family and I. There’s no better feeling after sitting on the chilly soccer sidelines than cozying up on our sofa in front of the fireplace I made, or taking a long shower after a long day of work in the shower I built and then curling up in the warm bed I painstakingly refinished. Knowing that I created a beautiful home that makes my family feel comfortable, safe, and loved feels so good. Right now we’re in a season of enjoying this home, but I am looking forward to the next season of creating. 

I love how my husband has taken this corner as his own - newest read on the floor, reading lamp he placed himself, and a notepad and pencil to jot down all the birds he sees from the window. 

#myhome2inspire #cottagestyle #countryhome #cljsquad #cottagedecor #cozyhome #diyhomedecor

Behold the Sister Suite Christmas tree!

Ever since I started designing this room, I imagined having a special Christmas tree in here for the girls. Last week I started looking for ornaments, not really knowing what I wanted for this tree, when one of my longtime Instagram followers, Dee messaged me that she would like to give me a collection of her vintage ornaments. They had been stored away for sometime, and she knew we would appreciate them. 

As the girls and I carefully unwrapped each ornament we were in complete disbelief at how beautiful they were- not to mention how perfectly they all coordinated with the Sister Suite. Emmeline had stopped believing in Santa some time ago, yet her face lit up with pure surprise and delight as she unwrapped a beautiful glass soccer ball ornament, creating absolute Christmas magic that only Santa seemed capable of. Every last ornament felt handpicked for us and so special. 

Thank you Dee for this special gift!

It’s hard to believe how much time has passed since this sweet little moment with my daughters, but I am very grateful that I thought to capture it in a painting. 

#girlmom #njmom #portraitpainting #currenthomeview #herviewfromhome #cljsquad #homesweethome

Started the year, by finishing a lingering art project. 

This painting not only represents a beautiful moment with my daughters, but also a time when I was really struggling to find my identity in the creative world. 

In 2019, after 14 years of employment, I lost a job that defined me - or so I thought. I put an unbelievable amount of creative energy into that job, and I really struggled with figuring out who I was without that job. I hadn’t really done anything creative outside of work, I had turned down freelance requests for years, and here I was, completely clueless on what to do with the talents and skills I had spent my entire life honing. Lost, depressed, and anxious, I sat before a blank canvas and picked up a paintbrush. (I’m now realizing how metaphorical that was). Working on the painting gave me the confidence to explore other creative endeavors, and sadly the painting got pushed to the back of the project stack. Since then I have stretched my wings and experimented with life as a shopkeeper, dabbled in graphics, web, landscape, interiors, floristry, influencing, styling, and probably some other things I’m forgetting. All of which led me to a beautiful lucidity of how I would like to use my talents for me, for others, and as a career (more on that soon). Cut to last month, when I started dreaming up an office space, specifically the art to hang in it. I have this idea for a quick painting, but I wasn’t going to let myself start a new painting without finishing the elephant in the room, the painting of the girls that has sat on my easel for years. I finished it, it’s framed, hung, I love it, and so proud of myself for finishing it, and for how much I have grown since I started it. Onto the next painting and an exciting new chapter for this creative lady. 

#mystory #currenthomeview #portraitpainting #creative #creativejourney
